The Generation 4 Mag Tactical Systems is made from magnesium alloy and is approximately 35% lighter than any aluminum lower receiver. These are new in unopened boxes. Only available in black.

FAQ - PLEASE READ! I am not going to respond to questions that are covered here!

Q. I am interested in your gun. Is it still available?
A. If you see this ad, most likely. The firearms are reserved for pickup on my web site, by making an appointment to buy. Someone 

could be doing it right now, and first person to reserve the firearm wins. Go to www.preciseshooter.com -> FAQ -> How to buy, read 

the requirements, and make the appointment on the site. If someone has made it just before you, I will notify you within a short 

time (usually, an hour), otherwise - see you shortly.

PLEASE DO NOT ASK WHETHER THE GUN IS STILL AVAILABLE! I WILL NOT RESPOND.

Q. How do I buy?
A. This is a dealer listing, NICS check, taxes, etc are all required. Please go to www.preciseshooter.com -> FAQ -> How to buy, read 

the requirements, and make the appointment to pick up.

Q. I am interested in your gun. Call me @ xxx-xxx-xxxx
A. Excellent. Go to www.preciseshooter.com -> FAQ -> How to buy, read the requirements, and make the appointment to pick it up.

Q. Are there any other fees, in addition to the price and taxes? NICS, background check, etc?
A. No.

Q. What is the tax rate?
A. 9.5% (WA only, of course, not applicable for out-of-state shipments)

Q. Where are you located?
A. Queen Anne neighborhood in Seattle.

Q. Can we meet in Burien on Monday morning?
A. No, FFL requirements are that the transfers happen at a licensed location. Also, the only times you can come over are the 

appointments that you can reserve on the site. No other time slots are available.

Q. I see you carry Savage rifles. Can you find me MKII FV-SR?
A. No. Please see here for what I can or cannot do: http://www.preciseshooter.com/NotInStock.aspx

Q. Do you take trades?
A. Sometimes. However:
a) firearms only,
b) they need to be our of current production (I can get new ones at wholesale prices), or you have to offer them to me at well below 

wholesale
c) I do not resell the trades, so they should fit my personal interests (which only include military as well as highly accurate, 

competition guns - no self defense guns like Glocks, M&Ps, XD*, and the like)
d) the exchange rate should be fair (see here for more: http://www.preciseshooter.com/blog/PriceGuide.aspx

Q. Is the price firm? Will you take XXX (70% of the asking price)?
A. The price is firm.

Q. Can you help me mount a scope/replace a trigger/fix a feeding problem?
A. Sorry, I do not do gunsmithing.

Q. Will you ship?
A. Yes - go to www.preciseshooter.com -> How to buy and read the section for buying outside Seattle area.

title: For Sale:  2 Mobiflex military tents $800 for the pair
postcontent:
I have 2 Mobiflex Military tents for sale.  1 command post and 1 crew shelter. 

The command post is what we used to camp in for the last couple years.  I'm not sure what the exact dimensions are, but it is big.  The rain fly and canvas have some small holes and rips in them, but could easily be patched.  We've used it in several storms without any leaks.  There were some rips/burns in the screens, but those have been patched. 

The crew shelter is the shorter one.  It's hardly been used (my wife preffered the command post because you could stand up in it).  The canvas, rain fly and screens are in perfect shape. 

There are enough hubs/lugs for one tent or the other.  The plastic lugs have been reinforced by drilling through them and adding a roll pin.  There are also has several aluminum lugs.  The 5 point hubs are the weak point in the system.  More can be purchased on Ebay, just search for Mobiflex and the auction will be in the results.  I will include all my spare parts(pins, bolts, extra lugs, extra 3 point hubs, etc.)

These tents are truely 4 season and will keep you warm and dry in any weather.  Either one will set up in minutes.  I'm moving to a small camper, so I no longer need either tent.  I pulled the photos off the internet to show what each looks like set up.

I'd take $550 for the Command Post, $300 for the Crew Shelter(without hubs), or $800 for both.

FTF Sale, these are too heavy to ship.
